Three Ekurhuleni Metro Police officers have been arrested for the alleged abduction of a Benoni supermarket owner. EKURHULENI - Three Ekurhuleni Metro Police officers have been arrested for the alleged abduction of a Benoni supermarket owner. It is alleged that the three officers from the Boksburg Truck Hijackings unit abducted the owner in July last year, and confiscated cigarettes worth R25,000. READ | Seven EMPD police officers arrested They demanded money and a cellphone from the owner, before releasing him near a freeway. The officers apparently filed false statements about the incident. They face charges of theft, kidnapping, extortion and defeating the ends of justice.